      • getStatus

        public java.lang.String getStatus()
        Gets the status. The status of the corpus: * `analyzed` indicates that the service has successfully analyzed the corpus; the custom model can be trained with data from the corpus. * `being_processed` indicates that the service is still analyzing the corpus; the service cannot accept requests to add new corpora or words, or to train the custom model. * `undetermined` indicates that the service encountered an error while processing the corpus.
        Returns:
        the status

      • getError

        public java.lang.String getError()
        Gets the error. If the status of the corpus is `undetermined`, the following message: `Analysis of corpus 'name' failed. Please try adding the corpus again by setting the 'allow_overwrite' flag to 'true'`.
        Returns:
        the error
